data.title: Category:Films shot at Associated British Studios
data.text:
Films shot in whole or in part at Associated British Studios, Shenley Road, Borehamwood, Hertfordshire, England (one of several studios known as Elstree Studios).

This category covers the period 1937–1970. The other Elstree studios that were also shooting films during this period were

Rock Studios/British National Studios (until 1958)

M.P. Studios/Gate Studios (until 1957)

New Elstree Studios (1956–1965)

MGM-British Studios (1944–1970).

For other films shot at the Shenley Road site see:
